definitions.definition: Late or failing to pay a debt or other financial obligation, like a mortgage or loan.
examples: Fred is delinquent in making his car payment.

definitions.definition: Of a payment or other financial obligation: late or otherwise unfulfilled.
examples: The company made a new effort to collect delinquent payments.

definitions.definition: Failing in or neglectful of a duty or obligation; guilty of a misdeed or offense
